abstract: The number of movers on the 1st of May seems to increase annually. Some "old fogies" call moving a relic of barbarism, and believe that a man who changes his residence every year or two is little better than the Ishmaelite, or the Indian who habitually pulled up his stakes once a week; but still the changing goes on.
